sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as 🌐 Client
    participant Gateway as 🚪 API Gateway
    participant JWT as 🔐 JWT Service
    participant SmartLinks as 🔗 SmartLinks
    participant MongoDB as 💾 MongoDB

    Note over Client,MongoDB: JWT Authentication Flow

    %% Login Flow
    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note right of Client: 1. Login & Get Token
        Client->>Gateway: POST /jwt/auth/login<br/>{username, password}
        Gateway->>JWT: POST /auth/login
        JWT->>MongoDB: Query users collection
        MongoDB-->>JWT: User data + password_hash
        JWT->>JWT: Verify password (bcrypt)
        JWT->>JWT: Generate Access Token (RS256, 10min)
        JWT->>JWT: Generate Refresh Token (RS256, 14d)
        JWT->>MongoDB: Store refresh_token
        MongoDB-->>JWT: OK
        JWT-->>Gateway: {access_token, refresh_token}
        Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK + Tokens
    end

    %% Authorized Request Flow
    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note right of Client: 2. Access Protected Resource
        Client->>Gateway: GET /my-private-link<br/>Authorization: Bearer {token}
        Gateway->>SmartLinks: GET /my-private-link
        SmartLinks->>SmartLinks: Parse DSL Rules
        Note over SmartLinks: AUTHORIZED -> private.com;<br/>LANGUAGE=en -> public.com
        SmartLinks->>Gateway: Fetch JWKS
        Gateway->>JWT: GET /.well-known/jwks.json
        JWT-->>Gateway: {keys: [...]}
        Gateway-->>SmartLinks: Public Keys
        SmartLinks->>SmartLinks: Validate JWT Token<br/>with RS256 Public Key
        alt Token Valid
            SmartLinks->>MongoDB: Query links (authorized rule)
            MongoDB-->>SmartLinks: DSL rules
            SmartLinks->>SmartLinks: Evaluate: AUTHORIZED = true
            SmartLinks-->>Gateway: 307 Redirect<br/>Location: private.com
        else Token Invalid
            SmartLinks->>SmartLinks: Evaluate: AUTHORIZED = false
            SmartLinks-->>Gateway: 307 Redirect<br/>Location: public.com
        end
        Gateway-->>Client: 307 Temporary Redirect
    end

    %% Refresh Token Flow
    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note right of Client: 3. Refresh Access Token
        Client->>Gateway: POST /jwt/auth/refresh<br/>{refresh_token}
        Gateway->>JWT: POST /auth/refresh
        JWT->>MongoDB: Query refresh_tokens
        MongoDB-->>JWT: Token data
        JWT->>JWT: Validate refresh token
        JWT->>JWT: Generate new access token
        JWT-->>Gateway: {access_token}
        Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK + New Token
    end
